To participate in Celo governance, community members can use several tools and platforms:Celo Mondo: A decentralized application for staking and governance, allowing users to lock CELO, vote on proposals, and earn rewards.

Celo Forum (forum.celo.org): The primary platform for discussing governance proposals and gathering community feedback.

Celo Governance GitHub (celo-org/governance): Hosts CGP documents and technical details for proposals.

Celo CLI: A command-line interface for technically proficient users to interact with the network and submit proposals.

Governance Calls: Community calls hosted by the Celo Foundation provide opportunities to present proposals, gather feedback, and network with stakeholders.

